1 0 0 1 50 742 Tm (# The Unit of Governance Is No Longer the Model) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 728 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 50 714 Tm (**Status:** final conceptual/methods draft) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 700 Tm (**Date:** 2026-05-03) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 686 Tm (**Theme:** agent-systems / governance / evaluation-benchmarking) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 672 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 50 658 Tm (## Abstract) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 644 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 50 630 Tm (AI governance discourse still often treats the model as the primary object to be governed.) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 616 Tm (In long-horizon, tool-using, memory-bearing agent systems, that framing is increasingly) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 602 Tm (inadequate. The relevant governed object is not the model alone but a broader **action) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 588 Tm (system**: the assembled socio-technical structure that mediates externally consequential) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 574 Tm (behavior through model inference, orchestration, tools, persistence, permissions, execution) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 560 Tm (environment, and oversight relations. This paper argues that many governance failures begin) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 546 Tm (with a prior conceptual error: they target the wrong unit. Unlike evaluation, which asks) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 532 Tm (what should be measured, attribution, which asks where an observed property belongs, and) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 518 Tm (control, which asks where feasible leverage resides, governance asks how authority, review) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 504 Tm (rights, accountability, and legitimate intervention are arranged around a system. On that) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 490 Tm (basis, this paper develops an action-system view of governance, analyzes where governance) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 476 Tm (power actually resides, shows why model-centered reporting under-describes deployed systems,) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 462 Tm (and proposes a governance-aware schema for serious claims about agent systems.) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 448 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 50 434 Tm (## 1. Introduction) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 420 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 50 406 Tm (A large fraction of current AI governance language still revolves around the model. The) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 392 Tm (model is benchmarked, documented, restricted, audited, and debated as if it were the) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 378 Tm (principal object through which advanced AI systems become governable.) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 364 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 50 350 Tm (That framing now lags behind practice.) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 336 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 50 322 Tm (Deployed agent systems increasingly operate through compound arrangements: a model is) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 308 Tm (embedded inside orchestration logic, memory policies, tool wrappers, permission gates,) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 294 Tm (runtime boundaries, logging infrastructure, approval rules, and human review structures.) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 280 Tm (What the system may do, what it may remember, which side effects it may trigger, who may) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 266 Tm (interrupt it, and who may later reconstruct what happened are often determined across these) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 252 Tm (layers rather than inside the model alone.) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 238 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 50 224 Tm (The main claim of this paper is therefore not merely that governance is difficult. It is) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 210 Tm (that governance is often aimed at the wrong object. If the governed unit is misidentified,) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 196 Tm (then authority will be assigned badly, oversight will attach to the wrong surface, audits) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 182 Tm (will under-describe the real system, and public claims about who is in charge will become) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 168 Tm (misleading.) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 154 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 50 140 Tm (The proposal developed here is that in long-horizon, tool-using, memory-bearing systems, the) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 126 Tm (relevant governed unit is increasingly the **action system**. By action system, we mean the) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 112 Tm (assembled socio-technical structure through which a model can produce externally) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 98 Tm (consequential behavior over time: perceiving context, recalling memory, planning steps,) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 84 Tm (invoking tools, requesting approvals, executing side effects, and persisting state.) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 70 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 50 56 Tm (### 1.1 Contributions) Tj
ET
endstream
