1 0 0 1 50 742 Tm (world. A model with the same weights can be embedded in a highly constrained, auditable,) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 728 Tm (interruptible regime or in a permissive, opaque, side-effect-capable one. If governance) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 714 Tm (remains centered mainly on the model, it will govern an important component while still) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 700 Tm (under-governing the practical system.) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 686 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 50 672 Tm (## 4. The Governed Unit Is the Action System) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 658 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 50 644 Tm (We define an **action system** as the assembled socio-technical structure that mediates) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 630 Tm (externally consequential behavior by connecting model outputs to memory, tools, permissions,) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 616 Tm (infrastructure, and oversight.) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 602 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 50 588 Tm (At minimum, an action system includes:) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 574 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 50 560 Tm (1. **The base model**) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 546 Tm (   Priors, local reasoning tendencies, and output generation.) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 532 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 50 518 Tm (2. **The orchestration layer**) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 504 Tm (   Decomposition logic, checkpoints, retries, escalation paths, continuation rules.) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 490 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 50 476 Tm (3. **The tool layer**) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 462 Tm (   APIs, file operations, messaging, browsing, shell or code execution, database access.) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 448 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 50 434 Tm (4. **The persistence layer**) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 420 Tm (   Memory stores, identity files, retrieval rules, summaries, retained traces.) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 406 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 50 392 Tm (5. **The permission and approval layer**) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 378 Tm (   Allowed actions, barred actions, approval thresholds, delegated authority.) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 364 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 50 350 Tm (6. **The execution environment**) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 336 Tm (   Sandboxes, credentials, network access, service bindings, infrastructure privileges.) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 322 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 50 308 Tm (7. **The oversight layer**) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 294 Tm (   Human reviewers, auditors, operators, rollback rights, deletion rights, stop rights.) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 280 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 50 266 Tm (This definition is intentionally operational rather than metaphysical. Its purpose is to) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 252 Tm (identify the object around which governance claims actually need to attach.) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 238 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 50 224 Tm (### 4.1 Boundary problems are part of the point) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 210 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 50 196 Tm (Action systems are not always cleanly bounded. In some cases the human approver feels) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 182 Tm (internal to the system; in others, more like an external governor. External APIs may) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 168 Tm (function as dependencies in one deployment but as integral action surfaces in another.) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 154 Tm (Account ownership may sit partly in infrastructure and partly in institutional policy.) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 140 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 50 126 Tm (That is not a flaw in the argument. It is one of its stakes. The governed unit is partly a) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 112 Tm (relational object. Governance must therefore account not only for components, but for) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 98 Tm (boundary-setting decisions: what is inside the governed assemblage, what is treated as) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 84 Tm (dependency, and who decides.) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 70 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 50 56 Tm (## 5. Where Governance Power Actually Resides) Tj
ET
