1 0 0 1 50 672 Tm (## 7. Worked Example: Governance Asymmetry with the Same Model) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 658 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 50 644 Tm (Consider two deployments of the same coding agent model.) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 630 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 50 616 Tm (### Condition A: opaque operator regime) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 602 Tm (- the model has shell and network access,) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 588 Tm (- memory persists across sessions,) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 574 Tm (- approvals for external actions are minimal,) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 560 Tm (- users cannot inspect or correct memory,) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 546 Tm (- audit logs are partial,) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 532 Tm (- credentials are held by the deployer,) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 518 Tm (- rollback is difficult.) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 504 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 50 490 Tm (### Condition B: reviewable operator regime) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 476 Tm (- tool access is explicitly bounded,) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 462 Tm (- high-risk actions require human approval,) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 448 Tm (- memory is inspectable and editable,) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 434 Tm (- logs are retained and reviewable,) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 420 Tm (- execution is checkpointed,) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 406 Tm (- rollback paths are explicit,) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 392 Tm (- authority boundaries are documented.) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 378 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 50 364 Tm (Suppose both systems use the same model and score similarly on benchmark tasks.) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 350 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 50 336 Tm (Even then, they are not governed in the same way. In Condition A, users and affected parties) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 322 Tm (face an opaque authority structure. The deployer controls memory, credentials, and runtime) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 308 Tm (power, while external observers may see only the model label. In Condition B, the same model) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 294 Tm (is embedded in a more contestable and reviewable governance regime.) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 280 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 50 266 Tm (The difference is not cosmetic. It affects who can challenge behavior, who can reconstruct) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 252 Tm (events, who can stop side effects, and who meaningfully holds power over system continuity.) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 238 Tm (Governance asymmetry therefore cannot be read off the model alone.) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 224 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 50 210 Tm (## 8. A Governance-Aware Reporting Schema) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 196 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 50 182 Tm (Any serious governance claim about an agent system should report at least:) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 168 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 50 154 Tm (1. **Base model** - exact model and inference regime.) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 140 Tm (2. **Orchestration** - decomposition logic, checkpoints, retries, escalation rules.) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 126 Tm (3. **Tools** - available actions, wrappers, side-effect boundaries.) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 112 Tm (4. **Persistence** - what memory exists, how it is retrieved, who may inspect, edit, or) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 98 Tm (delete it.) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 84 Tm (5. **Permissions** - action rights, approval thresholds, prohibited classes of actions.) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 70 Tm (6. **Infrastructure** - runtime boundaries, credentials, network limits, environment) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 56 Tm (privileges.) Tj
ET
