1 0 0 1 50 742 Tm (The action-system frame also raises hard boundary questions. In some cases it will be) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 728 Tm (contested which dependencies belong inside the governed unit and which sit outside it.) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 714 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 50 700 Tm (There is also a danger of governance inflation: not every wrapper deserves equal) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 686 Tm (significance. The argument is not that the model stops mattering, but that it stops being a) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 672 Tm (sufficient governance unit.) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 658 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 50 644 Tm (Finally, this paper only lightly treats deeper normative issues such as democratic) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 630 Tm (legitimacy, due process, and collective oversight. Those deserve fuller treatment later.) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 616 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 50 602 Tm (## 11. Conclusion) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 588 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 50 574 Tm (The main governance mistake in agent systems is increasingly not only weak oversight, but) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 560 Tm (oversight attached to the wrong object.) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 546 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 50 532 Tm (As systems become persistent, tool-bearing, orchestrated, and side-effect capable, the) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 518 Tm (relevant governed unit is no longer adequately described by the model alone. It is the) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 504 Tm (action system: the arrangement through which authority is exercised, permissions are) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 490 Tm (granted, memory is carried forward, interventions are routed, and traces are preserved or) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 476 Tm (hidden.) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 462 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 50 448 Tm (The sequence of questions now becomes clearer. Evaluation asks what is measured. Attribution) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 434 Tm (asks where properties belong. Control asks where leverage lives. Governance asks what) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 420 Tm (assembled object authority must attach to.) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 406 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 50 392 Tm (The practical question is therefore no longer only how to govern models. It is how to) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 378 Tm (identify, disclose, and govern the action system that actually acts in the world. Until that) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 364 Tm (unit is named correctly, governance claims about agent systems will remain partially) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 350 Tm (misdirected, and power will continue to hide in places our reporting frameworks treat as) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 336 Tm (implementation detail.) Tj
